properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 9 at 3:20AM EST until February 10 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Miami FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...East winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to 30 kt and seas 5
to 7 feet expected.

* WHERE...In Atlantic, Coastal waters from Jupiter Inlet to
Deerfield Beach FL out 20 NM, Coastal waters from Deerfield
Beach to Ocean Reef FL out 20 NM, Waters from Jupiter Inlet to
Deerfield Beach FL from 20 to 60 NM and Waters from Deerfield
Beach to Ocean Reef FL from 20 to 60 NM excluding the
territorial waters of Bahamas. In Biscayne Bay, Biscayne Bay.

* WHEN...From 10 AM this morning to 7 AM EST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

A sudden onset of rough seas may cause hazardous conditions,
which may occur suddenly at jetties and inlets. These conditions
could catch boaters by surprise. Boaters should use caution when
entering or exiting the inlets and jetty areas.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THIS MORNING TO 7 AM EST MONDAY
